  "prompt": "What is the true meaning of \"hear no evil, see no evil, speak no evil\"?",
  "response": "The phrase \"hear no evil, see no evil, speak no evil\" traditionally means to ignore impropriety, avoid engaging in malicious talk, and refrain from involving oneself in unethical actions. It is often embodied by the three wise monkeys: one covering its eyes, one covering its ears, and one covering its mouth. These actions symbolize a moral guideline of staying away from negative influences and maintaining innocence in thoughts and actions.\n\nIn a broader sense, some interpret the phrase as advocating for a mindful approach to life, encouraging individuals to focus on positivity and avoid dwelling on negativity. However, critics may argue that it implies turning a blind eye to wrongdoing or unethical behaviors, which can be problematic in situations where it is important to confront and address negative actions. Ultimately, the true meaning can vary depending on the context and personal interpretation.",
